In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims September 28, 2014, as Gold Star Mother's and Family's Day. He pays tribute to the mothers and families who have lost loved ones in the Armed Forces and acknowledges the sacrifices they have made for the nation. The president emphasizes the courage and resilience of Gold Star families and their commitment to preserving the memories of their fallen loved ones. He also calls upon government officials and the American people to display the flag and hold appropriate ceremonies to show gratitude and respect for Gold Star Mothers and Families.